This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a ceremony to award the Medal of Honor to Specialist Five James C. McCloughan. The president describes McCloughan's heroic actions during the Vietnam War, where he served as a combat medic. McCloughan risked his life multiple times to rescue wounded soldiers, even when he was injured himself. The president praises McCloughan's bravery and dedication to his fellow soldiers, and emphasizes the unbreakable spirit of America's military. The article concludes with the president presenting the Medal of Honor to McCloughan.